quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  8,22,The worst of beasts in Allah´s sight are the deaf and dumb who have no intellect
  8,23,"If Allah knew of any good in them, He would have made them able to hear. But even if He had made them able to hear, they would still have turned away"
  8,24,You who have iman! respond to Allah and to the Messenger when He calls you to what will bring you to life! Know that Allah intervenes between a man and his heart and that you will be gathered to Him
  8,25,Be fearful of trials which will not afflict solely those among you who do wrong. Know that Allah is severe in retribution
  8,26,"When you were few and oppressed in the land, afraid that the people would snatch you away, He gave you refuge and supported you with His help and provided you with good things so that hopefully you would be thankful"
  8,27,"You who have iman! do not betray Allah and His Messenger, and do not knowingly betray your trusts"
  8,28,Know that your wealth and children are a trial and that there is an immense reward with Allah
  8,29,"You who have iman! if you have taqwa of Allah, He will give you discrimination and erase your bad actions from you and forgive you. Allah´s favour is indeed immense"
  8,30,"When those who are kafir were plotting against you to imprison you or kill you or expel you: they were plotting and Allah was plotting, but Allah is the Best of Plotters"
  8,31,"When Our Signs are recited to them, they say, ´We have already heard all this. If we wanted, we could say the same thing. This is nothing but the myths of previous peoples.´"
  8,32,"And they say, ´Allah, if this is really the truth from You, rain down stones on us out of heaven or send a painful punishment down on us.´"
  8,33,Allah would not punish them while you were among them. Allah would not punish them as long as they sought forgiveness
  8,34,But why should Allah not punish them now when they bar access to the Masjid al-Haram? They are not its guardians. Only people who have taqwa can be its guardians. But most of them do not know that
  8,35,Their prayer at the House is nothing but whistling and clapping. So taste the punishment because you were kafir
  8,36,Those who are kafir spend their wealth barring access to the Way of Allah. They will spend it; then they will regret it; then they will be overthrown. Those who are kafir will be gathered into Hell
  8,37,"so that Allah can sift the bad out from the good, and pile the bad on top of one another, heaping them all together, and tip them into Hell. They are the lost"
  8,38,"Say to those who are kafir that if they stop, they will be forgiven what is past; but if they return to it, they have the pattern of previous peoples in the past"
  8,39,"Fight them until there is no more fitna and the deen is Allah´s alone. If they stop, Allah sees what they do"
  8,40,"but if they turn away, know that Allah is your Master, the Best of Masters, and the Best of Helpers"